217→WORKFLOW:
218→0. Understand Project
219→1. Read ./.claude/progress.txt and identify the most important pending task;
220→   - Specific task prioritization is indicated/tagged/prefixed with '[P'+number+']'
221→   - Tasks tagged with '[P0]' must be done before anything else.
222→   - Tasks tagged with P bigger than 999 (e.g. '[P1000]'), are low-priority
223→   tasks, they should be done when possible, but they must be done
224→   (they are not ignorable); If the task takes longer and there are other
225→   non-low-priority tasks, document progress and revert the status to "- [ ]".
226→
227→2. If NO pending tasks exist, plan next improvements, add tasks and stop
228→3. If there are tasks, mark it as IN_PROGRESS and then sequentially run:
229→   - Evaluate scope: if the task involves more than ~3 files or multiple concerns,
230→      break it into smaller sub-tasks in progress.txt BEFORE starting. Each sub-task
231→      must be completable in a single iteration (small, atomic, committable change).
232→   - Execute task
233→   - Run 'bun run check' and fix found issues.
234→   - Launch 1 review agents to deeply review the work, giving
235→      the entire context of the task, simulating pull request.
236→   - Review output and consider improvements
237→   - Implement corrections if needed
238→   - Update progress.txt marking task as completed
239→   - Commit task changes (not include unrelated code)
240→   - Output status block (see below)
241→   - Stop
242→
243→CRITICAL:
244→- ALL tasks and instructions are deliberate.
245→- No task is optional.
246→- If more work is necessary, add a new task to the file, set "exit": false, and Stop
247→- Never remove tasks, unless to update status;
248→- Never include workarounds and add tasks to fix all you found ('as any' for example is a workaround)
249→- No task should be submitted as "look reasonable."
250→- Every task must be delivered with professional quality, without any makeshift solutions.
251→- For tasks with visual parts, full visual and interaction tests with Playwright MCP are required.
252→- Never consider any mistake or error to be expected or acceptable.- Never consider any mistake or error to be expected or acceptable.
253→- Never trust project comments or documentation without confirming on actual
